# Context7 First

When working with PyMuPDF, pymupdf4llm, or Obsidian behavior, consult Context7
before relying on memory.

## Ground-truth domains

- PyMuPDF document/ToC/image APIs (`get_toc`, `metadata`, image extraction).
- pymupdf4llm `to_markdown` options (`page_chunks`, `write_images`,
  `image_path`) and the page-chunk return shape.
- Obsidian markdown conventions (wikilinks, frontmatter/properties) where a code
  detail depends on them.

## Discipline

- Verify exact tool/option names and return shapes against Context7 before
  prescribing pipeline changes.
- Cite resolved library IDs (see `docs/context7-index.md`), not free-text names.
- If Context7 cannot resolve a dependency, note it in `docs/context7-index.md`
  and fall back to first-party docs.
